            <thetext>Hi,

the python-toolchain currently doesn&#39;t support symbolic links. This is because the python method walk() handle them automatically.

From the python documentation (http://docs.python.org/lib/module-os.path.html):
&quot;Note: Symbolic links to directories are not treated as subdirectories, and that walk() therefore will not visit them. To visit linked directories you must identify them with os.path.islink(file) and os.path.isdir(file), and invoke walk() as necessary.&quot;

Please consider to support symbolic links in future versions of the python-scripts.</thetext>
